  "prompt": "How do you potty train a 4-month Pitbull?",
  "response": "Potty training a 4-month-old Pitbull requires patience, consistency, and positive reinforcement. Here are some tips:\n\n1. Establish a routine\n- Take your puppy outside frequently (every 1-2 hours)\n- Take them out first thing in the morning\n- After meals, naps, and playtime\n- Right before bedtime\n\n2. Choose a specific potty area\n- Always take your puppy to the same spot outside\n- This helps them associate that area with bathroom time\n\n3. Use positive reinforcement\n- Praise and treat your puppy immediately after they eliminate outside\n- Use a consistent verbal cue like \"go potty\"\n\n4. Crate training\n- Use a crate when you can't supervise\n- Dogs typically avoid soiling their sleeping area\n- Keep the crate appropriately sized\n\n5. Watch for signs they need to go\n- Sniffing\n- Circling\n- Whining\n- Restlessness\n\n6. Clean accidents thoroughly\n- Use an enzymatic cleaner to remove odors\n- Avoid punishing accidents\n\n7. Be patient and consistent\n- Puppies have limited bladder control\n- Accidents will happen\n- Stay positive and persistent\n\nRemember that every puppy learns at a different pace.",
